  "body": "**This is only a suggestion for improvements of your interface.**\r\nWhen you enter truffle console on a test or main network, it would be a huge time-saver to be able to specify the gasPrice of transactions automatically, due to differing transaction times and some transactions not passing at all.\r\n\r\nFor example : \r\nBy typing _contract.sendTransaction(10000)_,\r\nthe truffle console automatically appends _{gasPrice : 1100000000000}_ to the argument list,\r\nso as to make _contract.sendTransaction(10000, {gasPrice: 1100000000000})_.\r\n\r\nThis will make the interface a lot friendlier and quicker to use by ethereum developers.",
